        p
          | OK so what just happened here? We&apos;ve got the large button styled by Bootstrap listening for a click. Nothing else works until the button is clicked. Once it&apos;s clicked
          | you get a prompt for a positive non-zero integer with some JavaScript validating your input. I couldn&apos;t break it, but if you can please let me know. Once it&apos;s
          | got a valid entry the rest of the divs (again, styled by Bootstrap) are ready for their events (also a click, but it could be mouseover or something else). We&apos;re
          | replacing classes as we click on valid divs to change the background and border colors. We&apos;re also writing in not just text but HTML as you&apos;re moving along and
          | watching the JavaScript that I wrote play with your number. Retrieving the buttons and divs to have them listen for JavaScript events is based on the DOM which
          | I&apos;m not going to try to explain. If I could explain it well I&apos;d be teaching, not learning.
        p
          | We start by simply displaying your number. Then we apply a few basic operators to it. Then we get another number from you (with validation) and mash them together
          | in a few different ways. Then we run a little loop based on your number to create the next 1000 numbers in sequence. I displayed this in the console instead of
          | on the document itself to save your eyes. Next I converted your number to a string so I could find out how long it was, tell you the last digits, and insert
          | it as text into a link that I generated (I&apos;m actually super proud of this one). Last I started taking away from your number every second. This decrementing number
          | doesn&apos;t stop unless you stop the timer, which you do so by canceling the &quot;Go Again&quot; prompt. There&apos;s a lot going on here and it&apos;s a ton to try to explain. I added
          | my JavaScript as comments in this HTML file so go ahead and have a look at it. It&apos;s not very efficient (I could have used arrays for the div selectors,
          | maybe written a few more functions so I wouldn&apos;t have to repeat my code so much, and I have my variables in global scope because I couldn&apos;t ge them to work
